premise_source_doc_sentence: Howard Michael `` Howie '' Mandel  (  born November 29 , 1955  )  is a Canadian comedian , actor , television host , and voice actor .
He is well known as host of the NBC game show Deal or No Deal , as well as the show 's daytime and Canadian-English counterparts .
Before his career as a game show host , Mandel was best known for his role as rowdy ER intern Dr. Wayne Fiscus on the NBC medical drama St. Elsewhere .
He is also well known for being the creator and star of the children 's cartoon Bobby 's World .
Mandel became a judge on NBC 's America 's Got Talent , replacing David Hasselhoff , in the fifth season of the reality talent contest .

Mandel has mysophobia  (  an irrational fear of germs  )  to the point that he does not shake hands with anyone , including contestants on Deal or No Deal unless he is wearing latex gloves ; to that end , he prefers to do `` fist bumps '' instead .
The Howie Mandel Show is an American television variety show hosted by comedian Howie Mandel .
Howie Do It was a Canadian/American comedy television series , co-commissioned by Global and NBC , that stars Howie Mandel .
Howie Mandel  (  born 1955  )  , Canadian actor and comedian

Produced by Atlantis Communications for Showtime in the United States and CBC Television in Canada , the series starred comedian Howie Mandel alongside a supporting cast of comedians including Stephen Furst , Tim Bagley , Deborah Theaker , Jennifer Butt and Rob Cohen .
In April 2012 , NBC placed a seven-episode order for the show under the original title Howie Mandel 's White Elephant .
